{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889726207,"sessionID":"ses_284ba7171ffe43gCJs9LlNb0xx","part":{"id":"prt_d7b46b824001Mp934EnIwy6tym","messageID":"msg_d7b46ad4e001x2HbYvWFHPg2qL","sessionID":"ses_284ba7171ffe43gCJs9LlNb0xx","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_tool-417d278756ef48a59a99c58047179146","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/dify-plugin/ | grep -i change","description":"Check for CHANGE.md in plugin directory"},"output":"","metadata":{"output":"","exit":1,"description":"Check for CHANGE.md in plugin directory","truncated":false},"title":"Check for CHANGE.md in plugin directory","time":{"start":1775889726185,"end":1775889726205}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775889726213,"sessionID":"ses_284ba7171ffe43gCJs9LlNb0xx","part":{"id":"prt_d7b46bac9001LRIx94rhfIXDAA","messageID":"msg_d7b46ad4e001x2HbYvWFHPg2qL","sessionID":"ses_284ba7171ffe43gCJs9LlNb0xx","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-92ec574eaec747648cbc0909298d56f7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Integrations\n2: \n3: This directory contains integration modules for AgentCube, including plugins and connectors for external platforms.\n4: \n5: ## Dify Plugin\n6: \n7: The `dify-plugin/` directory contains a Dify-compatible plugin that enables AgentCube code interpreter functionality within the Dify platform.\n8: \n9: ### Overview\n10: \n11: The Dify plugin provides secure code execution and file management capabilities through AgentCube's sandboxed code interpreter environment. It allows Dify agents to execute Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript code in isolated Kubernetes pods.\n12: \n13: ### Features\n14: \n15: - **Multi-Language Support**: Execute code in Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript\n16: - **Secure Execution**: All code runs in isolated sandboxes with resource limits\n17: - **Session Management**: Reuse sessions for stateful operations\n18: - **File Operations**: Upload, download, and manage files\n19: - **Error Handling**: Comprehensive error reporting and recovery\n20: - **Dify Integration**: Seamless integration with Dify's tool framework\n21: \n22: ### Directory Structure\n23: \n24: ```\n25: dify-plugin/\n26: ├── main.py                          # Plugin entry point\n27: ├── manifest.yaml                    # Root plugin metadata\n28: ├── requirements.txt                 # Python dependencies\n29: ├── README.md                        # User documentation\n30: ├── GUIDE.md                         # Development guide\n31: ├── PRIVACY.md                       # Privacy policy\n32: ├── .difyignore                      # Packaging exclusions\n33: ├── icon.png / icon-dark.png         # Plugin icons\n34: ├── provider/\n35: │   ├── agentcube.yaml               # Provider descriptor\n36: │   └── agentcube.py                 # Provider implementation\n37: ├── tools/\n38: │   ├── agentcube-code-interpreter.yaml   # Tool schema\n39: │   └── agentcube-code-interpreter.py     # Tool implementation\n40: ├── tests/\n41: │   ├── test_provider.py            # Provider unit tests\n42: │   ├── test_tool.py                # Tool unit tests\n43: │   └── test_integration.py         # Integration tests\n44: └── examples/\n45:     ├── basic_usage.py              # Basic usage examples\n46:     └── advanced_usage.py           # Advanced usage examples\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Installation\n50: \n51: 1. **Install Dependencies**:\n52:    ```bash\n53:    cd dify-plugin\n54:    pip install -r requirements.txt\n55:    ```\n56: \n57: 2. **Package the Plugin**:\n58:    ```bash\n59:    zip -r agentcube-dify-plugin.zip . -x \"*.pyc\" \"__pycache__/*\" \"tests/*\" \"examples/*\"\n60:    ```\n61: \n62: 3. **Upload to Dify**:\n63:    - Navigate to Dify Settings -> Tools\n64:    - Click \"Import Plugin\"\n65:    - Select `agentcube-dify-plugin.zip`\n66: \n67: 4. **Configure the Tool**:\n68:    - Provide `router_url` (AgentCube Router service URL)\n69:    - Provide `workload_manager_url` (AgentCube Workload Manager URL)\n70:    - Optionally configure default language and interpreter settings\n71: \n72: ### Usage\n73: \n74: #### Basic Code Execution\n75: \n76: ```python\n77: {\n78:     \"router_url\": \"http://router.default.svc.cluster.local\",\n79:     \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://workload-manager.default.svc.cluster.local\",\n80:     \"language\": \"python\",\n81:     \"code\": \"print('Hello, World!')\"\n82: }\n83: ```\n84: \n85: #### Command Execution\n86: \n87: ```python\n88: {\n89:     \"router_url\": \"http://router.default.svc.cluster.local\",\n90:     \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://workload-manager.default.svc.cluster.local\",\n91:     \"command\": \"ls -la /tmp\"\n92: }\n93: ```\n94: \n95: #### Session Reuse\n96: \n97: ```python\n98: # First invocation\n99: {\n100:     \"router_url\": \"http://router.default.svc.cluster.local\",\n101:     \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://workload-manager.default.svc.cluster.local\",\n102:     \"code\": \"x = 10\"\n103: }\n104: \n105: # Second invocation with session_id\n106: {\n107:     \"router_url\": \"http://router.default.svc.cluster.local\",\n108:     \"workload_manager_url\": \"http://workload-manager.default.svc.cluster.local\",\n109:     \"session_id\": \"<previous_session_id>\",\n110:     \"code\": \"print(x * 2)\"\n111: }\n112: ```\n113: \n114: ### Testing\n115: \n116: Run all tests:\n117: ```bash\n118: cd dify-plugin\n119: python -m pytest -v\n120: ```\n121: \n122: Run with coverage:\n123: ```bash\n124: python -m pytest --cov=. --cov-report=html\n125: ```\n126: \n127: ### Development\n128: \n129: For detailed development information, see:\n130: - `dify-plugin/README.md`: User documentation and installation guide\n131: - `dify-plugin/GUIDE.md`: Development guide and best practices\n132: - `dify-plugin/examples/`: Usage examples\n133: \n134: ### Requirements\n135: \n136: - Python 3.12+\n137: - Dify platform\n138: - AgentCube cluster with Workload Manager and Router services\n139: - `dify-plugin>=0.4.2,<0.5.0`\n140: - `agentcube-sdk>=0.0.10`\n141: \n142: ### Architecture\n143: \n144: The plugin follows Dify's plugin architecture:\n145: \n146: ```\n147: Dify Platform\n148:     ↓\n149: Dify Plugin Framework\n150:     ↓\n151: Provider (Credential Validation)\n152:     ↓\n153: Tool (Code Interpreter)\n154:     ↓\n155: AgentCube SDK\n156:     ↓\n157: AgentCube Services (Router, Workload Manager)\n158:     ↓\n159: PicoD Sandbox (Kubernetes Pod)\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ### Security\n163: \n164: - All code execution occurs in isolated Kubernetes pods\n165: - Resource limits are enforced (CPU, memory)\n166: - Timeouts prevent runaway processes (default: 120s)\n167: - Sessions expire automatically (default TTL: 3600s)\n168: - Credentials are not logged\n169: - File paths are validated and sanitized\n170: \n171: ### Support\n172: \n173: For issues or questions:\n174: - GitHub: https://github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\n175: - Documentation: See `dify-plugin/` directory\n176: \n177: ## Additional Integrations\n178: \n179: Future integrations may be added to this directory as AgentCube expands its ecosystem.\n180: \n181: ## Contributing\n182: \n183: When contributing new integrations:\n184: 1. Follow the existing directory structure\n185: 2. Include comprehensive documentation\n186: 3. Add tests for new functionality\n187: 4. Ensure backward compatibility\n188: 5. Update this README\n189: \n190: ## License\n191: \n192: See the AgentCube project license for details.\n\n(End of file - total 192 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Integrations\n\nThis directory contains integration modules for AgentCube, including plugins and connectors for external platforms.\n\n## Dify Plugin\n\nThe `dify-plugin/` directory contains a Dify-compatible plugin that enables AgentCube code interpreter functionality within the Dify platform.\n\n### Overview\n\nThe Dify plugin provides secure code execution and file management capabilities through AgentCube's sandboxed code interpreter environment. It allows Dify agents to execute Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript code in isolated Kubernetes pods.\n\n### Features\n\n- **Multi-Language Support**: Execute code in Python, JavaScript, and TypeScript\n- **Secure Execution**: All code runs in isolated sandboxes with resource limits\n- **Session Management**: Reuse sessions for stateful operations\n- **File Operations**: Upload, download, and manage files\n- **Error Handling**: Comprehensive error reporting and recovery\n- **Dify Integration**: Seamless integration with Dify's tool framework","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/integrations/README.md","time":{"start":1775889726191,"end":1775889726211}}}}
